{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: source clients -> aggregation/orchestration -> summary input payload. Unit is too low because single-function tests can miss wiring/omission bugs across modules (MOCK-MISS). No real OS/network/subprocess is required to catch this specific failure if source adapters are stubbed in-process (REAL-INFRA no). Correctness here is payload completeness, not model judgment (LLM-DEP no). Not multi-agentic (MULTI-STEP no). Rejected higher level because behavior text only requires verifying included input data, not real endpoint behavior or LLM output quality.","test_description":"Run an integration test with three in-process fake source adapters returning distinct sentinel fields; execute report assembly through the real orchestration path; assert the exact payload sent to summary generation contains all three source sections and sentinel values.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.17,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module error propagation and fallback rendering: fetch failure from one source must propagate into report composition without terminating pipeline. Unit is too low because interaction between fetch/orchestrator/renderer is the failure surface. System is not required: unavailability can be reproduced by an in-process failing adapter, and behavior text does not require real network outage semantics. Agentic is not required because assertion is fallback note and continuation, not LLM quality.","test_description":"Use integration wiring with two successful fake sources and one fake source that raises timeout/unavailable. Execute report generation path and assert: (1) run completes, (2) output includes `data unavailable` marker only for failed section, (3) other sections remain populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior is explicitly about summary semantic accuracy, which depends on model generation quality (LLM-DEP yes). Deterministic stubs would hide hallucination/omission/paraphrase errors (MOCK-HIDE yes). Single-step model judgment is sufficient, so Workflow is not required (MULTI-STEP no). Rejected Integration because behavior text requires accuracy of generated narrative itself, not just routing/retry/format around the call.","test_description":"Run the real summary-generation model on curated fixtures with known key values and acceptance checks for factual fidelity (required values present, no contradictions, tolerated phrasing variance). Evaluate across repeated runs to detect nondeterministic miss rates and enforce a quality threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external delivery path and inbox receipt, which requires real HTTP/network/email infrastructure (REAL-INFRA yes). In-process mocks can falsely pass while DNS/auth/provider/inbox-routing issues fail in production (MOCK-HIDE yes). Although pipeline may include summarization, this behavior’s assertion is end-to-end delivery correctness, so real infra is the minimum boundary; model-output quality is not the primary oracle here.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end run in a system test environment against reachable test instances/endpoints and a real test mailbox. Assert recipient inbox receives one message with expected subject/body structure and that report content sections are present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core failure is orchestration/state persistence across runs: send failure -> local persistence -> next-run retry handoff. This is beyond single-function logic (MOCK-MISS yes). It can be caught with real local filesystem plus in-process failing/succeeding email adapter, without real external network or OS scheduler (invoke two runs directly), so System is not strictly required. Agentic/Workflow do not apply because correctness criterion is retry/persistence mechanics, not model decisions.","test_description":"Integration test using temp filesystem and controllable email adapter: first run forces send failure and asserts report persisted to fallback file/queue; second run simulates service recovery and asserts persisted report is retried and marked delivered/cleared.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.69,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
